No one hear owns or controls this site.  It is a dynamic entity that grows from those who contribute their thoughts. While we have no singular, private ownership..we do have a responsibility to nurture and protect this sight as we would a helpless child.<br>
It is a priviledge and a thing of beauty, to witness the sacred views and feelings of the veterans and non veterans who come here to personally document true history.<br>
There is an ongoing need to discuss trauma and its horrible impact..to search for reason and answers about the war..any war, and to share experience.  There is a need to extend a friendly, strong hand to veterans who waiver on the brink of despair and bring them into the realm of self dignity!<br>
A good steward is one who cares for something.  This site is worthy of care and protection.<br><br>
